        <Parent_String>spike fiddles [300196302], lutelike chordophones: bowed [300211800], lutelike chordophones [300224192], chordophones [300041641], sound devices by acoustical characteristics [300041621], sound devices (equipment) [300387677], Sound Devices (hierarchy name) [300041619], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Single-string spike fiddles of the Savanna area of West Africa, consisting of a half-kalabash resonator covered with monitor lizard skin with a hole on one side, a straight or curved wooden neck running through the resonator, a V- or Y-shaped wooden bridge, and a horsehair string.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000030041/Sadie, New Grove Dictionary of Musical Instruments (1984)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Vielles de una sola cuerda del área de Savana de Africa Occidental que consisten en un resonador de media calabaza cubierto con piel de lagarto con un orificio lateral, un mástil recto o curvo de madera que atraviesa el resonador, un puente de madera en forma de V o Y, y una cuerda de crin de caballo.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Spiesvedels met een halve kalebas als klankbodem, bedekt met varanenleer met een gat aan een kant, rechte of gebogen houten hals die door de klankboden loopt, een V- of Y-vormige houten kam, 1 snaar van paardenhaar; West Afrikaanse savannegebied.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052488/Etnomusicologisch Centrum</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指西非莽原地區的單弦釘狀琴腳提琴，具單邊有孔、覆有巨蜥蜴皮的半葫蘆狀共鳴器、穿過共鳴器，或直或彎的木製琴頸、V形或Y形的木製琴橋、及一根馬鬃製的琴弦。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Einsaitige Spießgeige der Savannenregion Westafrikas, die aus einer halben Kalebasse als Resonanzkörper besteht, bedeckt mit Waranenhaut und mit einer Öffnung an jeder Seite, einem geraden oder gebogenen Hals aus Holz, der durch den Resonanzkörper führt, einem V- oder Y-förmigen Steg und einer Rosshaarsaite.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
